{
  "stem": "2581.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So being we had two breads, we would cut up one bread in eight pieces, so we had the other one for the next four days.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I remember my father cutting the pieces and then this one had a little lump, so we had to straighten out the lump.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he'd get a piece for me and a piece for him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And no, it's not straight, it has another lump.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we kept smoothing out that piece of bread, too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By the time it was the ration for the next day, it was a quarter of what was intended to be.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we were hungry the next day, and we kept straightening out these little pieces of bread.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We used to get to our rations-- we would get at one time rad-- radishes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's in Yiddish called [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Radish.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I made rice from that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would cut it on a-- on a-- what is it called?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A grater.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Put it five times into hot water and then take a pinch of flour, burn the flour, and give it a little color with water and salt, and we were eating and it-- we filled up our stomachs.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But from all these and I-- and my father kept saying, where did you learn to cook?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It just, you know, it comes to you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Necessity, I think, is the best teacher, it was the mother of invention.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Never, never, never.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Never.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like, my father wouldn't let me into the factory, not to become a tailor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I certainly couldn't be in the kitchen-- no one could be in the kitchen when mother-- when mother cooked.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But one thing in particular what I remember, the rations were getting smaller.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
